; Position to column
;
; Used by the routines at #R$949D and #R$9516.
;
; .
;
; Convert a 16-bit fixed-point position (e.g. #R$60BA, the actor's column
; position -- 4 sub-units per tower column) into a coarse column index: A = HL
; >> 2, computed as a proper 16-bit shift (H's low bits feed into A) so the
; result isn't just the high byte.
; .
; In: HL = fixed-point position.
; .
; Out: A = column index (HL >> 2), HL preserved.
; .
; Clobbers: A.
@label=pos_to_col
c$9493 PUSH HL       ; save HL (preserve caller's position)
 $9494 LD A,L        ; A = L (low byte of position)
 $9495 SRL H         ; H >>= 1, carry = H's old bit0
 $9497 RRA           ; A = (A>>1) with carry in from H -- 16-bit shift, pass 1
 $9498 SRL H         ; H >>= 1 again, carry = bit0
 $949A RRA           ; A = (A>>1) with carry in -- 16-bit shift, pass 2 (A =
                     ; HL>>2)
 $949B POP HL        ; restore HL
 $949C RET           ;

